    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe content in the viewport, viewport position, is not the same as I left it when switching back to previous buffer. Instead it seems to be centered as much as possible.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:edit foo (which is a scrollable document)\r\nPut the cursor in, for instance, the second last line in the viewport.\r\n:edit bar\r\n:bn\r\nThe cursor is on the correct line, but the viewport has been scrolled to show it at the vertical center/middle.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would like to keep the viewport position not having to readjust it.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0-dev-2795+g1b55ed58e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
